It's the third day of former president Jacob Zuma's testimony at the Zondo Commission. Zuma has so far made sensational claims of senior ANC leaders being aparteid spies, and threats to his and his family's lives. JOHANNESBURG - Former president Jacob Zuma will appear at the state capture on Wednesday. Zum has rubbished testimonies of two previous witnesses, who claimed he had a hand in their redeployment or dismissal as per the Guptas' wishes. Day 2: Zuma's testimony full of 'I don't know' He also told the commission that he feels vilified and revealed that he has received death threats. Zuma's testimony is set down for five days.